 the sample with 5, 9, 11, 13, and 15 plutonium\nplates had the high almost identical values of KC while the sample with 3\nplates had by one-third smaller KC values than all the others. These\ncalculations were supplemented by the Lypaunov exponents for a time series and\nthe NIST tests. The low KC values can be addressed to the different sources of\nuncertainties in measuring procedure with the sample consisting of three\nplates.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sun, 14 Mar 2021 21:10:43 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-04-28"}
