lated by the seasonal variability of the relative\nhumidity, airmass and seeing. Using the scatter of the [O~III] $\\lambda$5007\nfluxes emitted from the narrow-line region of active galactic nuclei as an\nindicator, we found that the correction accuracy of the telluric absorption\nlines is 1%.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 15 Mar 2021 04:56:14 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-09-08"}
